text:
If you don't need HTTPS, that's

```<VirtualHost *:80>
    ServerName <http://myprograms.com|myprograms.com>
    DocumentRoot "C:/path/to/myprograms"
    # Additional settings here, such as ErrorLog, CustomLog...
</VirtualHost>```

text:
As for https, you add a `VirtualHost *:443`  block, with the same settings plus

```SSLEngine on
SSLCertificateFile C:\path\to\certificate\file.pem
SSLCertificateKeyFile C:\path\to\certificate\key.pem
# Handle old IE versions with poor SSL support
BrowserMatch "MSIE [2-6]" \
    nokeepalive ssl-unclean-shutdown \
    downgrade-1.0 force-response-1.0
BrowserMatch "MSIE [17-9]" ssl-unclean-shutdown```
